The InterGroup Foundation â€“ Upward Bound program will continue to help these students and more. The directors said that 20% of the population of Palau goes off-island to make their living, and will return at one time or another to the island, looking for a good place to settle, and raise their families.

At the time of our visit the new building for the InterGroup Foundation's Upward Bound was still under construction, and expecting to be completed by the end of this year. The room featured in the photos was built as a repurposed concrete structure, and helped to save construction costs.

Gina, shown and originally from New Mexico, came to Palau by way of Guam to become one of the staff for the Upward Bound program. She was full of accolades for her student staff, and was anxious to get them involved in real life problem solving of the day.

The High School students are also involved in field trip adventure races, called Whatâ€™s In The Bag Races, which seem to have the students involved in every aspect of discovery and invention.
